airship-event##airship:offsetID##descrip: An identifier that represents the events location in the Airship event stream and can be used for troubleshooting or handling duplicate events.
airship-event##airship:localeVariant##de: The language locale variant if one is reported for the device..
airship-event##airship:uaSdkVersion##des: The version of the Airship SDK used in the app.
airship-event##airship:attributes##descr: Attributes specific to devices in Airship.
airship-event##airship:pushID##descripti: A unique identifier for a push operation.
airship-event##airship:groupID##descript: Identifies a push delivered over an interval of time, e.g. multiple push_ids as part of the fulfillment of an automation or a push-to-local-time specification.
airship-event##airship:variantID##descri: The ID of the variant that a push is associated with, if the push was a part of an A/B test (experiment).
airship-event##airship:alerting##descrip: If true, the send event was alerting. Alerting send event has notification text, badge, or sound.
airship-event##airship:categories##descr: An array of categories that must have between 1 and 10 elements, each of which is a string with a 64-byte limit.
airship-event##airship:campaigns##descri: An object listing the campaigns a push specification is associated with.
airship-event##airship:campaign##descrip: An object listing the campaigns a push specification is associated with. The campaigns object includes an array of categories that must have between 1 and 10 elements, each of which is a string with a 64-byte limit.
airship-event##airship:pushTime##descrip: The UTC time when the push occurred.
airship-event##airship:triggeringPush##d: The specific push notification details associated with an event. An associated push helps you trace an event to the original notification or operation.An associated push object may specify a `time`, if the push was a singular operation sent at a defined time. Otherwise, the object will include a `group_id` if the push was sent at a relative time (`best_time` or `local_time`) an automation pipeline, or another operation resulting in multiple `push_id`s.
airship-event##airship:lastDelivered##de: Identifies the last push notification the audience received before the event. Absent if the last push occurred more than 12 hours ago.
airship-event##airship:complianceEventTy: The type of compliance event for proving data-safety regulation compliance for email and SMS channel-related events.
airship-event##airship:messageType##desc: The message type that the user unsubscribed from
airship-event##airship:registrationType#: The type of change to a registration status.
airship-event##airship:commercialOptedIn: The date and time when the user opted into commercial email messages.
airship-event##airship:bounceClass##desc: The bounce classification as provided by Airship email partners.
airship-event##airship:bounceSender##des: The address that the bounced email came from (typically the sender address for your project in Airship).
airship-event##airship:bounceSubject##de: The subject line of the bounced email.
airship-event##airship:compliancePropert: Additional properties for a compliance event.
airship-event##airship:regionAction##des: Indicates whether the event was the result of a user entering or exiting the region.
airship-event##airship:regionName##descr: A friendly name for the region or geofence; may be provided from a third-party location partner.
airship-event##airship:regionID##descrip: The unique region identifier from the originating system or location partner.
airship-event##airship:body##description: Contains Airship specific event body fields.
airship-event##description: Airship gathers engagement data that can help you better understand how your audience uses and reacts to your apps and messages. This mixin groups standard mixins that can be used describe Airship's standard engagement events. Any non-standard fields should be added as needed.
identity-graph-flattened-export##xdm:ide: Person ID Like Email or ECID or phone.
identity-graph-flattened-export##xdm:nam: Identity Type in human readable form.
identity-graph-flattened-export##xdm:alg: Algorithm used by Identity Service to stitch like SHARED_DEVICE_DETECTION_SESSIONIZATION, DETERMINISTIC, FREQ_RECENCY etc.
identity-graph-flattened-export##xdm:las: Last updated time when this identity was updated.
identity-namespace##xdm:namespaceName##d: This is human readable name for the namespace
identity-namespace##xdm:namespaceCode##d: This code is a human readable identifier for the namespace
identity-namespace##xdm:namespaceIdType#: Identity identifier type for the namespace
identity-namespace##xdm:createDate##desc: The date and time when the namespace was created in ISO 8601 format
identity-namespace##xdm:modifyDate##desc: The date and time when the namespace was updated in ISO 8601 format
person-name##xdm:firstName##description: The first segment of the name in the writing order most commonly accepted in the language of the name. In many cultures this is the preferred personal or given name. The `firstName` and `lastName` properties have been introduced to maintain compatibility with existing systems that model names in a simplified, non-semantic, and non-internationalizable way. Using `xdm:fullName` is always preferable.
person-name##xdm:lastName##description: The last segment of the name in the writing order most commonly accepted in the language of the name. In many cultures this is the inherited family name, surname, patronymic, or matronymic name. The `firstName` and `lastName` properties have been introduced to maintain compatibility with existing systems that model names in a simplified, non-semantic, and non-internationalizable way. Using `xdm:fullName` is always preferable.
person-name##xdm:middleName##description: Middle, alternative, or additional names supplied between the first name and last name.
person-name##xdm:courtesyTitle##descript: Normally an abbreviation of a persons title, honorific, or salutation. The `courtesyTitle` is used in front of full or last name in opening texts. For example, Mr. Miss. or Dr.
person-name##xdm:suffix##description: A group of letters provided after a person's name to provide additional information. The `suffix` is used at the end of someones name. For example Jr., Sr., M.D., PhD, I, II, III, etc.
person-name##xdm:fullName##description: The full name of the person, in writing order most commonly accepted in the language of the name.
person##xdm:birthDate##description: The full date a person was born.
person##xdm:birthDayAndMonth##descriptio: The day and month a person was born, in the format MM-DD. This field should be used when the day and month of a person's birth is known, but not the year.
person##xdm:birthYear##description: The year a person was born including the century, for example, 1983.  This field should be used when only the person's age is known, not the full birth date.
person##xdm:maritalStatus##description: Describes a person's relationship with a significant other.
person##xdm:nationality##description: The legal relationship between a person and their state represented using the ISO 3166-1 Alpha-2 code.
person##xdm:taxId##description: The Tax / Fiscal ID of the person, e.g. the TIN in the US or the CIF/NIF in Spain.
person##description: An individual person. May represent a person acting in various roles, such as a customer, contact, or owner.
